For the wideband analysis, recorded LFPs were downsampled and pairwise correlated using Pearson’s correlation coefficient. To study the functional connectivity at specific frequency bands, LFPs were also zero-phased bandpass filtered with a Butterworth filter. The resulting 32 × 32 matrices of each individual were used as input for the Louvain method for community detection and average shortest path analysis adapted from [30]. For the shortest path calculations, a conversion between correlation strength (Wij) and distance (Dij) was performed as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
